DataElement.preferredName: Insulin Dependent Diabetes Mellitus Present Year Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the numeric representation of the calendar year as related to dependence on insulin (human insulin protein (110 aa, 12 kDa), encoded by the human insulin (INS) gene, is produced in pancreatic islet beta cells and regulates protein and lipid metabolism as well as decreases blood glucose concentration by shuttling molecules into cells to be used for energy.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to dependence on insulin (human insulin protein (110 aa, 12 kDa), encoded by the human insulin (INS) gene, is produced in pancreatic islet beta cells and regulates protein and lipid metabolism as well as decreases blood glucose concentration by shuttling molecules into cells to be used for energy.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Diabetes mellitus characterized by insulin deficiency, sudden onset, severe hyperglycemia, rapid progression to ketoacidosis, and death unless treated with insulin. The disease may occur at any age, but is most common in childhood or adolescence.

Concepts.definition: A chronic condition characterized by minimal or absent production of insulin by the pancreas.
